abstract_ssm: The Hornstein collection documents the work of a prominent Chaucerian and English scholar whose entire career developed at New York University. The collection contains Hornstein's research material on Chaucer's literature, including correspondence, bibliographical indexes, manuscripts, papers and articles.
subject_ssm: English literature |x Middle English, 1100-1500 |x History and criticism |v Addresses, essays, lectures.
